$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{v_{\text {out }}}{v_{1}} \equiv-A=-g_{\mathrm{m} 1} R_{2} \tag{4.139}
\end{equation*}
$$

The admittance $Y$ bridging $v_{1}$ and $v_{\text {out }}$ is $Y(s)=s C_{g d 1}$. Hence, we have

$$
\begin{equation*}
Y_{1}(s)=s C_{g d 1}(1+A)=s C_{g d 1}\left(1+g_{m 1} R_{2}\right) \tag{4.140}
\end{equation*}
$$

