The prevalent method for analyzing common-source amplifiers to ascertain their -3 dB frequency relies on the Miller theorem. This theorem posits that the two circuits depicted in Fig. 4.15 are equivalent if $Y_{1}$ and $Y_{2}$ are appropriately selected. Specifically, if

$$
\begin{equation*}
